# Optimize PromptLab Analyzer with Niche Prompt Structures & Universal Frameworks

Enhance the analyzer engine so that it (a) recognises niche prompt categories, (b) applies universal prompt frameworks as evaluation criteria, and (c) produces **significantly more detailed, longer, and actionable** optimised output.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Niche-Specific Task Categories

Currently the engine detects 9 task intents: `explain`, `compare`, [generate](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js#2175-2178), `summarize`, [analyze](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js#1164-1549), [list](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js#1800-1817), `instruct`, `code`, `brainstorm`.

**Add 4 new niche intents** drawn from the user's document:

| New Intent | Trigger Keywords |
|---|---|
| [plan](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/app.js#690-694) | plan, schedule, routine, milestone, workflow, productivity, habit, goal |
| [story](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/local-db.js#143-151) | story, fiction, narrative, character, plot, scene, arc, theme |
| `content` | SEO, article, blog, content calendar, headline, draft, engagement |
| `evaluate` | evaluate, diagnose, improve, critique, review, iterate, refine |

#### Files Changed

##### [MODIFY] [promptlab-engine.js](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js)

**a) `TASK_PATTERNS` array** (~line 1148) â€” append the 4 new pattern objects.

**b) Niche blueprints for every model** (~line 771â€“1110) â€” add [plan](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/app.js#690-694), [story](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/local-db.js#143-151), `content`, `evaluate` blueprints under each of `openai`, `anthropic`, `gemini` with tailored `required`, `recommended`, `optional`, and `tips` arrays derived from the reference document. Each `tips` array will have **4â€“6 entries** (currently 3â€“4) to provide richer feedback.

**c) Niche-specific suggestions** â€” extend [_generateSuggestionForElement](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js#1691-1795) and [_suggestFormat](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js#1922-1965) / [_suggestScope](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js#1966-1980) / [_suggestTone](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js#1991-2000) helpers to cover the 4 new tasks.

---

### 2. Universal Framework Detection & Scoring

Add a new structural element **`framework`** that checks whether the prompt uses any recognised universal framework pattern:

| Framework | Detection Pattern |
|---|---|
| Roleâ†’Taskâ†’Contextâ†’Constraintsâ†’Output | role/persona keyword + task verb + context + constraint + format |
| Clarify-first | "ask clarifying questions", "before responding" |
| Evaluateâ†’Diagnoseâ†’Improve | evaluate + diagnose/identify + improve/fix |
| Compare-justify | "compare" + "justify" + "best" |
| Iterative refinement | "v1", "critique", "improve to v2", "iterate" |
| Step-by-step reasoning | "step by step" + "assumptions" |
| Output-first | "output:" before main body |
| Critic+Creator | "critic", "creator", "dual role" |
| Teach-beginner | "explain as if teaching a beginner", "ELI5" |
| Advise-expert | "advise an expert", "expert-level" |

This will be added as:
- A new `ELEMENTS.FRAMEWORK` entry
- A new `DETECTION.framework` block with patterns + [qualityCheck](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js#594-601)
- Listed as `recommended` in `general` blueprints across all models
- A **bonus pattern** per model for framework usage (+0.4 model_alignment)

---

### 3. More Detailed & Longer Suggestions

Currently [_buildSuggestions](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js#1674-1690) is capped at **max 3** suggestions. Changes:

- Increase cap from 3 â†’ **5** suggestions
- Each suggestion's `improved` field will be much longer: instead of appending a single line, it will provide a **full rewritten prompt** incorporating the missing element naturally into the existing text
- Add a new `detailedExplanation` field per suggestion explaining *why* this change matters for the target model
- Enhance [_buildRewriteHint](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js#1818-1887) templates to be **3â€“4Ă— longer**, embedding the user's reference structures (e.g., `Role â†’ Task â†’ Context â†’ Constraints â†’ Output Format`) with placeholder guidance

---

### 4. Enhanced Educational Summary

Extend [_buildIntentExplanation](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/public/js/promptlab-engine.js#1630-1669) to output **a multi-paragraph explanation** instead of the current 4â€“6 sentence summary. The new version will:

- State detected intent + niche category (if applicable)
- Identify which universal framework the prompt most closely resembles
- Explain which elements are present/missing with **specific model-context reasoning**
- Provide a **"Next Steps" paragraph** listing the top 3 improvements ranked by impact

---

